Description: Pottery lamp of Frog Type, with rounded carination. Top shows a frog; crescent over nozzle. Undefined base; crossed branch patterns, impressed or incised; below, a crescent. Red-brown, micaceous clay; buff surface over large area.
Curator's comments: Close: Shier, L.A., 1978. ‘Terracotta Lamps from Karanis, Egypt’. Ann Arbor : University of Michigan Press, 216, from Karanis (context-date: late third to early fourth century AD) ; Brants, J., 1913. ‘Antieke terra-cotta lampen uit het Rijksmuseum van oudheden te Leiden’. Leiden : Rijksmuseum, 1071; Petrie, W.M.F., 1905. ‘Roman Ehnasya (Herakleopolis Magna) 1904’. London : Egypt Exploration Fund, pl. lxiii, f 58; Anthes, R., 1959. ‘Mit Rahineh 1955’.
